ose engaged in the study of history to direct more attention to the fundamental questions of truth, morality, and meaning.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aDiscipline. 0aDiscussion. 0aEthics. 0aHistoriography. 0aHistory-Philosophy. 0aHistory. 0aJudgment (Ethics). 0aMethodology. 0aPhilosophy. 0aPostmodernism. 0aRelativity. 0aTruth. 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh  aattaining historical truth.  adiscipline.  adiscussion.  ahistorical studies.  ahistory.  ameaning.  amethodology.  amoral judgment.  amorality.  aphilosophy.  apost-truth.  apostmodernism.  apurpose.  arelativism.  astudy.  astudying history.  atheory.  atruth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753038940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487530389423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487530389.jpg  a978-3-11-065206-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles